WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:01.964
Your app runs,

00:00:01.964 --> 00:00:04.212
but only the server can see it.

00:00:04.212 --> 00:00:06.782
Let's give it a real domain with automatic

00:00:06.782 --> 00:00:07.103
TLS.

00:00:07.103 --> 00:00:08.067
Four short steps,

00:00:08.067 --> 00:00:09.673
and it's on the internet.

00:00:10.461 --> 00:00:12.151
Here is the path:

00:00:12.151 --> 00:00:14.264
grab a Cloudflare API token,

00:00:14.264 --> 00:00:16.800
configure the infrastructure once on the

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:17.222
CLI,

00:00:17.222 --> 00:00:19.335
push it to the server,

00:00:19.335 --> 00:00:21.870
then deploy a small proxy repo

00:00:21.870 --> 00:00:24.406
that handles DNS and certificates for

00:00:24.406 --> 00:00:24.828
you.

00:00:25.287 --> 00:00:25.724
First,

00:00:25.724 --> 00:00:27.473
the one manual step.

00:00:27.473 --> 00:00:29.222
Open the Cloudflare dashboard,

00:00:29.222 --> 00:00:30.971
go to My Profile,

00:00:30.971 --> 00:00:32.283
then API Tokens,

00:00:32.283 --> 00:00:34.906
and create a token with Zone

00:00:34.906 --> 00:00:36.218
DNS Edit permission.

00:00:36.218 --> 00:00:38.841
That single token lets the CLI

00:00:38.841 --> 00:00:40.590
manage your DNS records,

00:00:40.590 --> 00:00:43.214
so you never click through dashboards

00:00:43.214 --> 00:00:43.651
again.

00:00:46.734 --> 00:00:49.534
Step two. We set the public IP, the

00:00:49.534 --> 00:00:52.254
base domain, the certificate email, and

00:00:52.254 --> 00:00:55.054
the Cloudflare API token from the command line

00:00:55.454 --> 00:00:58.254
. The cert email and the token are shared across all

00:00:58.254 --> 00:01:00.974
your machines, so you only set them once.

00:01:03.179 --> 00:01:05.339
Infrastructure recorded in your config.

00:01:08.812 --> 00:01:11.692
Let us confirm the infrastructure settings were stored

00:01:12.092 --> 00:01:15.052
. Public IP, base domain, certificate

00:01:15.052 --> 00:01:16.572
email, all visible.

00:01:18.451 --> 00:01:20.771
Settings stored. Ready to push to the server.

00:01:24.120 --> 00:01:24.981
Step three:

00:01:24.981 --> 00:01:27.564
push the configuration to the server.

00:01:27.564 --> 00:01:30.147
With a real token this creates

00:01:30.147 --> 00:01:32.730
your DNS records on Cloudflare automatically

00:01:32.730 --> 00:01:34.882
and prepares the proxy configuration.

00:01:35.762 --> 00:01:38.402
Pushed. DNS records are being created

00:01:38.402 --> 00:01:39.282
on Cloudflare.

00:01:42.665 --> 00:01:43.467
Step four:

00:01:43.467 --> 00:01:45.875
create a small repo named infra.

00:01:45.875 --> 00:01:47.481
Why its own repo?

00:01:47.481 --> 00:01:50.290
The proxy routes traffic for every app

00:01:50.290 --> 00:01:51.494
on this server.

00:01:51.494 --> 00:01:53.902
Infrastructure deserves its own isolated box,

00:01:53.902 --> 00:01:55.909
away from your application code.

00:01:59.309 --> 00:02:02.349
Infra repo created. Isolated from your app repos.

00:02:05.794 --> 00:02:08.354
Apply the proxy template. It carries Traefik

00:02:08.354 --> 00:02:11.074
plus the configuration for Let's Encrypt and Cloudflare

00:02:11.154 --> 00:02:13.394
DNS-01 challenges, ready to go.

00:02:16.677 --> 00:02:18.357
Traefik configuration in place.

00:02:21.748 --> 00:02:24.548
And bring the proxy up. Traefik discovers

00:02:24.548 --> 00:02:27.588
your containers automatically. TLS certificates

00:02:27.588 --> 00:02:30.228
come from Let's Encrypt automatically. Your

00:02:30.308 --> 00:02:33.588
app is now reachable on the internet over HTTPS.

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:39.430
Proxy is live. TLS certificates

00:02:39.430 --> 00:02:40.710
will arrive automatically.

00:02:41.621 --> 00:02:44.341
And that's networking sorted! See

00:02:44.341 --> 00:02:45.381
you in the next one.
